                            <comment id="16477586" author="jcttrll" created="Wed, 16 May 2018 15:37:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;An ugly workaround is to replace the B.super.doSomething() call with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt;.forName(A.name + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;$Trait$Helper&apos;&lt;/span&gt;).getMethod(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;doSomething&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, A).invoke(A, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17762839" author="emilles" created="Thu, 7 Sep 2023 18:35:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;A.super.doSomething()&quot; would succeed if the checks in ResolveVisitor did not reject &quot;A&quot; due to indirect implements.  For &quot;B.super.doSomething()&quot; to succeed, a change is required in SuperCallTraitTransformer where it produces &quot;B$Trait$Helper.doSomething(this)&quot; or in the production of the B$Trait$Helper class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17763248" author="emilles" created="Fri, 8 Sep 2023 20:01:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/cef3a2c1d0d59ccd1071e155df8ea133fbb813c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/cef3a2c1d0d59ccd1071e155df8ea133fbb813c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
